[0.000, "o", "    \u001b[1;34m\"originalLine\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;39m6\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[1;34m\"path\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;32m\"docs/blog-announcement.md\"\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;39m}\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;39m{\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[1;34m\"body\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;32m\"There is an empty top-level Markdown heading (`#`) immediately after the frontmatter. This typically renders as a blank H1 and can interfere with page structure/TOC; consider removing it or replacing it with an actual heading.\\n```suggestion\\n# Announcing gh-observer: Because Waiting for CI Should Not Be a Mystery\\n```\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[1;34m\"originalLine\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;39m12\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[1;34m\"path\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;32m\"docs/blog-announcement.md\"\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;39m}\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;39m{\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[1;34m\"body\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;32m\"Typo: “somereal” should be “some real”.\\n```suggestion\\nThe standard `gh pr checks --watch` has had some real gaps for a while now:\\n```\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[1;34m\"originalLine\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;39m28\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b["]
