[0.000, "o", "    \u001b[1;34m\"body\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;32m\"The README includes both `gh extension install ...` and `go install ...`, but the Usage section now only shows `gh observer`. For users installing via `go install` (or running the built binary directly), the command is typically `gh-observer`; consider documenting both invocation styles or adding a short note mapping install method → command.\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[1;34m\"originalLine\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;39m116\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[1;34m\"path\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;32m\"README.md\"\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;39m}\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;39m{\u001b[0m\r\n"]
