[0.011, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[38;5;130m  1 \u001b[0m+++\u001b[106C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m  2 \u001b[0mtitle = 'Announcing gh-observer: Because Waiting for CI Should Not Be a Mystery'\u001b[29C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m  3 \u001b[0mdate = 2026-03-08T02:00:00-00:00\u001b[77C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m  4 \u001b[0mdraft = false\u001b[96C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m  5 \u001b[0mdescription = 'I Got Tired of Watching \u001b[35m`\u001b[0mgh pr checks --watch\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m Fail Me, So I Built Something Better'\u001b[10C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m  6 \u001b[0mcover.image = '/posts/2026-FIX.png'\u001b[74C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m  7 \u001b[0mcover.hidden = false\u001b[89C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m  8 \u001b[0mkeywords = [\"github-actions\", \"github-cli-extension\"]\u001b[56C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m  9 \u001b[0mtags = [\"github\", \"programming\"]\u001b[77C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 10 \u001b[0mShowToc = true\u001b[95C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 11 \u001b[0m+++\u001b[106C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 12 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 13 \u001b[0mLook, I know what you're thinking: \"Another dev scratched their own itch and\u001b[33C\u001b[48;5;22"]
[0.000, "o", "4m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 14 \u001b[0mnow they want to tell me about it.\" Guilty. But hear me out, because this\u001b[36C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 15 \u001b[0mparticular itch has probably been annoying you too, and the scratch is\u001b[39C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 16 \u001b[0mgenuinely useful.\u001b[92C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 17 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 18 \u001b[0m\u001b[35m## \u001b[0m\u001b[35mThe Problem Nobody Talks About\u001b[0m\u001b[76C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 19 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 20 \u001b[0mHere's the scenario that broke me: I push a PR, immediately run \u001b[35m`\u001b[0mgh pr checks\u001b[32C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 21 \u001b[0m--watch\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m, and... it bombs out with an error because GitHub Actions hasn't\u001b[36C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 22 \u001b[0mqueued anything yet. So I wait. I run it again. Maybe it works, maybe it\u001b[37C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 23 \u001b[0mdoesn't. And when it finally does start showing me checks, I'm staring at a\u001b[34C\u001b[48;5;224m "]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 24 \u001b[0mlist of job names with no idea whether that \u001b[35m`\u001b[0m3m 52s\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m I've been waiting is\u001b[36C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 25 \u001b[0mnormal or a sign that something's silently wedged.\u001b[59C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 26 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 27 \u001b[0mThe standard \u001b[35m`\u001b[0mgh pr checks --watch\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m has had somereal gaps for a while now:\u001b[35C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 28 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 29 -\u001b[0m \u001b[1m**It doesn't handle startup delay.**\u001b[0m GitHub Actions typically takes 30-90\u001b[34C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 30 \u001b[0m  seconds to queue jobs after a PR is created or pushed to. The built-in\u001b[37C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 31 \u001b[0m  watcher just... gives up during that window.\u001b[63C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 32 -\u001b[0m \u001b[1m**No queue latency.**\u001b[0m You can see a job is \"in progress,\" but you have no\u001b[34C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 33 \u001b[0m  idea if it's been sitting in a queue for 2 seconds or 45 seconds before it\u001b[33C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[3"]
[0.000, "o", "8;5;130m 34 \u001b[0m  started.\u001b[99C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 35 -\u001b[0m \u001b[1m**No runtime metrics.**\u001b[0m Is that job that's been \"running\" for a while\u001b[38C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 36 \u001b[0m  actually running, or has GitHub just not updated the status yet? Who knows!\u001b[32C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 37 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 38 \u001b[0mSo naturally, I did what any reasonable developer does when something annoys\u001b[33C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 39 \u001b[0mthem enough: I spent way more time building a solution than I would have lost\u001b[32C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 40 \u001b[0mjust dealing with the annoyance. Classic.\u001b[68C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 41 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 42 \u001b[0m\u001b[35m## \u001b[0m\u001b[35mIntroducing gh-observer\u001b[0m\u001b[83C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 43 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 44 \u001b[0m\u001b[35m`\u001b[0mgh-observer\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m is a GitHub CLI extension that replaces \u001b[35m`\u001b[0mgh pr checks --watch"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m\u001b[33C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 45 \u001b[0mwith something that actually tells you what's going on. It's a full TUI\u001b[38C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 46 \u001b[0m(terminal UI) that polls GitHub's API every 5 seconds and shows you the\u001b[38C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 47 \u001b[0minformation you actually care about.\u001b[73C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 48 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 49 \u001b[0mHere's what a typical run looks like:\u001b[72C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 50 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 51 \u001b[0m\u001b[35m```ShellOutput\u001b[0m\u001b[95C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 52 \u001b[0mPR #5: 🔶\u001b[52;15H[claude] /init 21:04:15 UTC\u001b[72C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\u001b[53;105H1,1\u001b[11CTop\u001b[1;5H\u001b[34h\u001b[?25h"]
