[0.000, "o", " Actions workflows / actionlint      8s\u001b[51C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 65 \u001b[0m  39s ✓ Checkov\u001b[41C2s\u001b[51C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 66 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 67 \u001b[0mPress q to quit\u001b[94C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 68 \u001b[0m\u001b[35m```\u001b[0m\u001b[106C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 69 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 70 \u001b[0mThat \u001b[35m`\u001b[0m15s\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m in the Startup column? That's how long GitHub sat on the job before\u001b[31C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 71 \u001b[0mactually starting it. The \u001b[35m`\u001b[0m3m 52s\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m at the end? That's the total runtime. Now\u001b[33C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 72 \u001b[0myou know the Claude review is just slow, not broken.\u001b[57C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 73 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 74 \u001b[0m\u001b[35m## \u001b[0m\u001b[35mThe Startup Phase Thing\u001b[0m\u001b[83C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 75 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 76 \u001b[0mThis is the part I'm most proud of, honestly. Instead of bombing out when there"]
[0.002, "o", "\u001b[30C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 77 \u001b[0mare no checks yet, \u001b[35m`\u001b[0mgh-observer\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m shows you a helpful waiting message:\u001b[40C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 78 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 79 \u001b[0m\u001b[35m```ShellOutput\u001b[0m\u001b[95C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 80 \u001b[0mPR #123: Add new feature\u001b[85C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 81 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 82 \u001b[0mStartup Phase (37s elapsed):\u001b[81C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 83 \u001b[0m  ⏳\u001b[33;10HWaiting for Actions to start...\u001b[73C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 84 \u001b[0m  💡\u001b[34;10HGitHub typically takes 30-90s to queue jobs after PR creation\u001b[43C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 85 \u001b[0m\u001b[35m```\u001b[0m\u001b[106C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 86 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 87 \u001b[0mIt tracks how long you've been waiting, reminds you that this is normal, and\u001b[33C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 88 \u001b[0mjust... keeps watching. No manual intervention required. No re-running the\u001b[35C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 89 \u001b[0mcommand. It transitions smoothl"]
[0.001, "o", "y into showing actual check status once jobs\u001b[34C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 90 \u001b[0mstart appearing.\u001b[93C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 91 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 92 \u001b[0m\u001b[35m## \u001b[0m\u001b[35mFeatures Worth Knowing About\u001b[0m\u001b[78C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 93 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 94 \u001b[0m\u001b[1m**Queue latency and runtime metrics**\u001b[0m are the headline features, but there's more:\u001b[27C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 95 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 96 -\u001b[0m \u001b[1m**Workflow/Job naming**\u001b[0m —\u001b[46;33HInstead of just the job name, you see \"MarkdownLint\u001b[30C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 97 \u001b[0m  / lint\" so you know which workflow the job belongs to. Uses GitHub's GraphQL\u001b[31C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 98 \u001b[0m  API to pull this efficiently in a single query.\u001b[60C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 99 -\u001b[0m \u001b[1m**Error log integration**\u001b[0m —\u001b[49;35HFailed checks show the first line of their error\u001b[31C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m100 \u001b[0m  output right there in the terminal. No m"]
[0.000, "o", "ore clicking through to GitHub to\u001b[34C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m101 \u001b[0m  find out \u001b[3m*why*\u001b[23m something failed.\u001b[75C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m102 -\u001b[0m \u001b[1m**Rate limit awareness**\u001b[0m —\u001b[52;34HWhen you're getting close to GitHub API limits, it\u001b[30C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\u001b[53;105H51,1\u001b[10C37%\u001b[1;5H\u001b[34h\u001b[?25h"]
