[0.005, "o", "\u001b[52;33H\u001b[1;52r\u001b[1;1H\u001b[6M\u001b[1;53r\u001b[47;1H\u001b[38;5;130m 53 \u001b[0mUpdated 0s ago  •\u001b[47;24HPushed 43h 8m 11s ago\u001b[69C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 54 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 55 \u001b[0mStartup   Workflow/Job\u001b[32CDuration\u001b[47C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 56 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 57 \u001b[0m  15s ✗ MarkdownLint / lint\u001b[29C5s\u001b[51C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m 58 \u001b[0m   .github:13 - Failed with \u001b[103mexit\u001b[0m code: 1\u001b[69C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\u001b[53;1H\u001b[K\u001b[53;105H58,29\u001b[10C4%\u001b[52;33H\u001b[34h\u001b[?25h"]
[0.609, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[53;95Hj\u001b[52;33H"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[53;95H \u001b[52;5H\u001b[1;52r\u001b[52;1H\r\n\u001b[1;53r\u001b[52;1H\u001b[38;5;130m 59 \u001b[0m\u001b[109C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\u001b[53;105H\u001b[K\u001b[53;105H59,0-1\u001b[9C5%\u001b[52;5H\u001b[34h\u001b[?25h"]
[0.369, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[53;95Hj\u001b[52;5H"]
[0.002, "o", "\u001b[53;95H \u001b[52;33H\u001b[1;52r\u001b[52;1H\r\n\u001b[1;53r\u001b[52;1H\u001b[38;5;130m 60 \u001b[0m  15s ✓ Auto Assign / run\u001b[31C5s\u001b[51C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\u001b[53;105H\u001b[K\u001b[53;105H60,31-29\u001b[7C6%\u001b[52;33H\u001b[34h\u001b[?25h"]
[0.197, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[53;95Hj\u001b[52;33H"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[53;95H \u001b[52;33H\u001b[1;52r\u001b[52;1H\r\n\u001b[1;53r\u001b[52;1H\u001b[38;5;130m 61 \u001b[0m  15s ✓ CUE Validation / verify\u001b[25C6s\u001b[51C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\u001b[53;105H\u001b[K\u001b[53;105H61,31-29\u001b[7C7%\u001b[52;33H\u001b[34h\u001b[?25h"]
[0.180, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[53;95Hj\u001b[52;33H"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[53;95H \u001b[52;33H\u001b[1;52r\u001b[52;1H\r\n\u001b[1;53r\u001b[52;1H\u001b[38;5;130m 62 \u001b[0m  15s ✓ Checkov / scan\u001b[33C27s\u001b[51C\u001b[48;5;224m \u001b[0m\u001b[53;105H\u001b[K\u001b[53;105H62,31-29\u001b[7C7%\u001b[52;33H\u001b[34h\u001b[?25h"]
[0.279, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[53;95Hn\u001b[52;33H"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n/exit\u001b[53;95H\u001b[K\u001b[53;1H"]
[0.002, "o", "\u001b[27;54H\u001b[1;2H\u001b[38;5;130m80\u001b[0m\u001b[1CPR #123: Add new feature\u001b[2;2H\u001b[38;5;130m81\r\n 82\u001b[0m\u001b[1CStartup Phase (37s elapsed):                                                \u001b[4;2H\u001b[38;5;130m83\u001b[0m\u001b[1C  ⏳\u001b[4;9H Waiting for Actions to start...                                     \u001b[5;2H\u001b[38;5;130m84\u001b[0m\u001b[1C  💡\u001b[5;9H GitHub typically takes 30-90s to queue jobs after PR creation    \u001b[6;2H\u001b[38;5;130m85\u001b[0m\u001b[1C\u001b[35m```\u001b[0m              \u001b[7;2H\u001b[38;5;130m86\r\n 87\u001b[0m\u001b[1CIt tracks how long you've been waiting, reminds you that this is normal, and\u001b[9;2H\u001b[38;5;130m88\u001b[0m\u001b[1Cjust... keeps watching. No manual intervention required. No re-running the\u001b[10;2H\u001b[38;5;130m89\u001b[0m\u001b[1Ccommand. It transitions smoothly into showing actual check status once jobs  \u001b[11;2H\u001b[38;5;130m90\u001b[0m\u001b[1Cstart appearing.                                                         \u001b[12;2H\u001b[38;5;130m91\u001b[0m\u001b[1C                                                                        \u001b[13;2H\u001b[38;5;130m92\u001b[0m\u001b[1C\u001b[35m## \u001b[0m\u001b[35mFeatures Worth Knowing About\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "                                            \u001b[14;2H\u001b[38;5;130m93\u001b[0m\u001b[1C                                                                         \u001b[15;2H\u001b[38;5;130m94\u001b[0m\u001b[1C\u001b[1m**Queue latency and runtime metrics**\u001b[0m are the headline features, but there's more:\u001b[16;2H\u001b[38;5;130m95\r\n 96 -\u001b[0m \u001b[1m**Workflow/Job naming**\u001b[0m —\u001b[17;32H Instead of just the job name, you see \"MarkdownLint\u001b[18;2H\u001b[38;5;130m97\u001b[0m\u001b[3C/ lint\" so you know which workflow the job belongs to. Uses GitHub's GraphQL\u001b[19;2H\u001b[38;5;130m98\u001b[0m\u001b[1C  API to pull this efficiently in a single query.                          \u001b[20;2H\u001b[38;5;130m99 -\u001b[0m \u001b[1m**Error log integration**\u001b[0m —\u001b[20;35HFailed checks show the first line of their error\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m100\u001b[0m\u001b[3Coutput right there in the terminal. No more clicking through to GitHub to\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m101\u001b[0m\u001b[1C  find out \u001b[3m*why*\u001b[23m something failed.                                         \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m102 -\u001b[0m "]
[0.002, "o", "\u001b[1m**Rate limit awareness**\u001b[0m —\u001b[23;33H When you're getting close to GitHub API limits, it\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m103\u001b[0m\u001b[3Cautomatically backs off and polls less frequently. Keeps your rate limit\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m104\u001b[0m\u001b[1C  healthy without any manual configuration.                            \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m105 -\u001b[0m \u001b[1m**CI-friendly snapshot mode**\u001b[0m —\u001b[26;39HWhen stdout isn't a TTY (like in a script or\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m106\u001b[0m\u001b[3Cpipeline), it prints a plain text snapshot and \u001b[103mexit\u001b[0ms with an appropriate \u001b[103mexit\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m107\u001b[0m\u001b[1C  code. So \u001b[35m`\u001b[0mgh-observer && deploy.sh\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m actually works.                       \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m108 -\u001b[0m \u001b[1m**Configurable colors**\u001b[0m —\u001b[29;32H ANSI 256-color support via                       \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m109\u001b[0m\u001b[1C  \u001b[35m`\u001b[0m~/.config/gh-observer/config.yaml\u001b[35m`\u001b[0m if you're particular about your terminal\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m110\u001b[0m\u001b[3Caesthetics.\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m111\u001b[0m\u001b[1C                          \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m112\u001b[0m\u001b[1C\u001b[35m## \u001b[0m\u001b[35mInstallation\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[3"]
[0.000, "o", "8;5;130m113\u001b[0m\u001b[1C                                                                            \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m114\u001b[0m\u001b[1CThe easiest path is the precompiled binary via GitHub CLI extensions —\u001b[35;75H no Go\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m115\u001b[0m\u001b[1Ctoolchain required:                                                    \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m116\u001b[0m\u001b[1C                                    \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m117\u001b[0m\u001b[1C\u001b[35m```bash\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m118\u001b[0m\u001b[1Cgh extension install fini-net/gh-observer\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m119\u001b[0m\u001b[1C\u001b[35m```\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m120\u001b[0m\u001b[1C              \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m121\u001b[0m\u001b[2Crecompiled binaries exist for macOS (Intel and Apple Silicon), Linux (x86-64\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m122\u001b[0m\u001b[1Cand ARM64), and Windows (x86-64). All binaries include build attestations for\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m123\u001b[0m\u001b[1Csupply chain security verification.\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m124\u001b[0m\u001b[1C                      \u001b[32C        \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m125\u001b[0m\u001b[1C\u001b[35m## \u001b[0m\u001b[35mHow to Use It\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;130m126\u001b[0m\u001b[3C                         "]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[29C  \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m127\u001b[0m\u001b[1CAuto-detect your current branch's PR:   \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m128\r\n129\u001b[0m\u001b[1C\u001b[35m```bash\u001b[0m                  \u001b[31C  \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m130\u001b[0m\u001b[1Cgh observer                    \u001b[25C  \r\n\u001b[38;5;130m131\u001b[0m\u001b[1C\u001b[35m```\u001b[0m                   \u001b[33C   \u001b[53;105H106,50\u001b[8C62%\u001b[27;54H\u001b[34h\u001b[?25h"]
